Dependency Graph Summary:
The graph shows that src.flask_app is the central entry point of the application, depending on all three sibling modules: src.load_data, src.query_data, and src.scrape. src.db sits at the top of the hierarchy as a shared utility, providing the get_connection() function to both src.load_data and src.query_data. This design eliminates code duplication and centralises all database credential logic in one place. src.scrape is an independent module with no database dependency — it only handles HTTP requests and HTML parsing via requests and beautifulsoup4. src.load_data handles INSERT operations into PostgreSQL, relying on src.db for its connection. src.query_data handles all SELECT/analysis queries, also using src.db for its connection. The architecture is clean with no circular dependencies and a clear separation of concerns across scraping, loading, querying, and routing layers.